eal good points.<br>
<br>
It's a very realistic view of a paladin/sk fight, couple of minor tweaks - though i am more of an oldschool dualer but will include some new tricks to.<br>
<br>
lv9-49 <br>
I would wager the shadowknight winining every fight.<br>
ATK, STR debuffs really hamper the paladins DPS by a lot at those lvs, most people wont have high Strength or Attack.. and a simple strength buff can encumber the unaware paladin easy (worse before lv30 armor as most armor/wepons are heavy) and an encumbered paladin is very easy to hit and doesnt hurt you much.<br>
<br>
50+ is when it gets fun, most have very good selection of Resist armors, Tanking armors, wepon selections and utility items.<br>
<br>
Shadowknight spell damage is misleading, Dots/taps in PvP are Very mana in-efficent..... healing is the same efficency if in PvP or out of PvP.<br>
     If i waste all my mana doing Dots - then i wont have mana to lifetap, then when the end of a fight comes i watch the paladin Lay hands or root and back out ot heal to full with me left at 30% hit points and 10% mana.<br>
<br>
Ac on paladin and shadowknight is equal, bear in mind we have AC buffs/Debuffs - that will debuff you and give to us.. these debuffs are configurable so give or take a point or two we are above/under paladin AC... so fairly equal there.<br>
<br>
We can dispell yours buffs and you ours, however the shadowknight has a lot of reasonably low cost buffs that he can junk on him self and debuff you on a 1.5 second cast. So debuffing an shadowknight is a loosing battle - they will just laughat you, while a shadowknight will happily dispell your buff knowing you cant recast it.<br>
<br>
Pets, once feared are not an issue, flash of light/spook undead, often pets go wierd in duals anyway - but can be quite good.<br>
<br>
About the best way to beat a paladin is keep stunning him as he trys to heal - sometimes you can get scared paladins to chain heal and keep getting interupted, wich is when they blow there mana trying to out distance you - meaning you can get lots and lots of free damage.<br>
<br>
Lifetaps do damage also but at 2/3rd there rate so really use them to heal not do damage.<br>
<br>
Saying all this i would love to fight an AAed up paladin at 60 (once i get a bucket load of AA of course) it would be interesting to see if me and my pet if it survives can do enough damage to kill a paladin with all there extreemly low cast time heals....... the new heals are so nice i really do think i would have trouble in the fight.... WICH is great, so far paladins have been push overs and only at 50+ do they begin to challenge you.<br>
<br>
Braellar <p>&lt;img src=&quot;http://eqsighost.netfirms.com/Braellarth/sig_02.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bjond>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1509<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/11/02 5:42:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=110.topic&index=53>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> If you're serious about BotB ..</span><hr size=1> .. then get a big 2H weapon -- largest damage and delay you can -- and learn to joust and strafe.  Gore may consider that &quot;cheese tactics&quot;, but all the winners of the BotB use it and are damn good at it.  Carry pumice stones and use them to knock off any self-buffs.  Carry regen and healing potions.  Carry a DS potion in case he's dumb and uses a pair of fast weapons and doesn't joust.  Carry invis potions and wear a see-invis item or carry a bracer of the hidden.  Get run-3 and jboots.  Get a fungi tunic.  Change the color of the message for when someone else uses a discipline.  Make sure it's a unique color.  Setup an emote hotkey of your own to confuse the enemy and make him think you burned your /disc.  After all that, practice over and over and over.<br>
<br>
Gear helps a ton, but it's not only about gear.  Blitzberg from Tunare in the team BotB couple years ago took out 4 of the FoH team members solo after they had killed off 5 of his team.  They were in NtoV gear with primal.  He was using PoG armor and Kunark weapons.<br>
<br>
BTW, some BotB have special rules, like no-clickies permitted at all.  In that case, you're down to regen, joust, strafe, and disciplines.  Practice using the rules you'll be fighting under. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aailin>Aailin </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 169<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/26/02 2:22:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=110.topic&index=54>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: If you're serious about BotB ..</span><hr size=1> Well as far as dueling a Paladin POP has turned Paladins from good pvp'ers to great ones.<br>
With the addition of the new fast casting heals IE Nife 900hp <br>
.75 cast time to augment CC 1.5 second cast time Paladins can get off many nearly uninteruptable heals.<br>
Your best bet is prolly to dispell a paladin so CC will fall in his first slot that way you can Dispell it before he gets full benefit of it.<br>
With Wis of 150 I can cast CC about 11 times during a fight with no FT items. So your looking at roughly another 9k in hps you have to wade through on top of LH. <br>
If you let a paladin blow his mana fully healing himself he's winning. End of story.<br>
Paladins are very buff realiant dispelling them is a must.<br>
I myself when I duel always keep some pumice nice and hot keyed and dispell off the top<br>
<br>
Btw as Bakanome said Fear the Paladin with a soulfire.  Unless you gonna burn him down you will not win that fight.<br>
5 instant cast Cheals cannot be beaten.<br>
